"url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95060997/1910-11-04/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_electrum_ver02/data/sn95060997/00517018934/1910110401/0253.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95060997/1910-11-04/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["az_electrum_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/arizona/", "2/united states/arizona/cochise/", "3/united states/arizona/cochise/willcox/"], "contributor": ["arizona state library, archives and public records; phoenix, az"], "date": "1910-11-04", "dates": ["1910-11-04"], "description": ["Arizona Range News VOL XVII MASCOT COPPER ISSUES ANNUAL REPORT HAS BEEN MAILED TO STOCKHOLDERS SUBSTANTIAL CONDITIONS AT PROPERTY This Company is Developing What is Destined to be One of the Biggest Copper Mines in the Country AN UNUSUAL PROPERTY More Like a Manufacturing Enterprise Than a Mining Enterprise as Generally Un derstood and Will Be a Great Wealth Producer For Many Generations One of the most satisfactory reports ever issued by a mining company has been mailed to stockholders by the Mascot Copper Company following the annual meeting of the corporation at Chicago on October 3rd A perusal of the report which appears in this issue of the Arizona Range News should prove a source of intense satisfaction to all who have shown their faith in the magnificent property of Mascot Copper by making investments in the shares of the company now operating in Dos Cabezas in the heart of the greatest copper zone of the United States Although the company has not yet reached the producing stage the official report just sent to the stockholders shows that the property is being de veloped and equipped in a substantial and permanent manner preparatory to taking its place among the"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-04-06T23:45:25.558Z", "group": ["ndnp/az"